- "Most robust daily trading volume" refers to the highest average daily trading volume;
- "Crowned by the stock" means the stock with the highest average daily volume in its sector;
- "Market domains" refers to the sectors in the stock market.

- Market capitalization is a measure of a company's size and value, calculated by multiplying the number of outstanding shares by the current stock price;
- Sectors and industries are used to classify companies based on their primary business activities;
- The query ranks sector-industry combinations based on the average market capitalization of the companies within them.

- "shining beacon" refers to the stock that ranks first based on its performance metrics;
- "standing tall with the highest cumulative peak of its closing prices" indicates the stock with the highest cumulative sum of maximum closing prices over the specified period (2020-01-01 to 2023-12-31);
- "over the past four years" specifies the date range from 2020-01-01 to 2023-12-31.

- "Dynamic top performers" refers to stocks with high average daily price changes;
- "Top 3 stocks by market capitalization" means the three largest companies in terms of market value within each sector;
- "Average daily change" is calculated by averaging the daily price changes of the stock over a period.

- 'users' refers to individuals identified by `user_id`;
- 'eyes on the scenery' refers to access events where `access_type` is 'view';
- 'unique vantage points' refers to the number of unique IP addresses (`ip_address`);
- 'total time spent gazing' refers to the sum of the duration of access sessions (`duration`).

- 'Blossoms of attention' refers to the average access duration of views;
- 'Bloom time' refers to the duration of access sessions;
- 'Gentle gazes lasting more than a minute' means access sessions longer than 60 seconds;
- 'Average bloom time' refers to the overall average access duration across all access logs.

- 'giants of the market' refers to companies with a market capitalization greater than 100 billion;
- 'bird's-eye view' implies these users have accessed or interacted with these large companies;
- 'graphical representation of data' refers to the presence of 'graph' type widgets in their dashboards.

- 'Rising stars' refers to companies whose stock prices have increased;
- 'Shining brighter with each passing day' refers to the days when the stock price increased;
- 'Stellar gains' refers to the percentage of days the stock price increased.
